# Review Prep Engine - Cursor Context Rules

## Project Overview
Building a modern wealth management client review preparation system with:
- Automated briefing generation from CRM, custodial, and planning data
- Engagement scoring and cohort analysis
- n8n workflows for daily sync and weekly reminders
- Trigger.dev jobs for async processing
- React Email templates for notifications
- Supabase for relational data and RLS policies

## Core Domain Concepts

### Households
- Top-level entity representing client relationship
- Contains multiple members (spouse, dependents, POAs)
- Track engagement metrics, historical performance, review preferences
- Has assigned advisor(s)

### Portfolios & Positions
- Household may have multiple accounts across custodians (Schwab, Fidelity, etc.)
- Each account has positions (equities, bonds, funds, alternatives)
- Track cost basis, performance, contribution history
- Compute deltas from last review to identify changes

### Briefings
- Generated documents created before client meetings
- Contain: household summary, portfolio overview, performance analysis, action items
- Track creation time, last modified, advisor email sent timestamps
- Historical versions maintained for review continuity

### Action Items
- Tasks identified during reviews or ongoing engagement
- Status tracking: pending, in_progress, completed, deferred
- Follow-up dates, assignee, client communication status
- Link to specific review or engagement moment

### Engagement Scoring
- Historical scoring for households over time
- Factors: activity frequency, meeting attendance, portfolio changes, communication
- Cohort classification: premier, core, growth, at_risk
- Predictive indicators for attrition risk

### Meeting History
- Record of all client interactions
- Meeting notes, attendees, agenda items covered
- Link to generated briefings and outcomes

## Technical Architecture

### Data Layer (Supabase)
- PostgreSQL with Row Level Security (RLS)
- Advisors: see only assigned households
- Compliance officers: see all households
- Admins: full management access
- Real-time subscriptions for briefing status updates

### Integration Layer (n8n)
- CRM sync: Salesforce API → local data
- Custodial sync: Direct API or file import from Schwab, Fidelity, etc.
- Change detection: Compare current vs. last sync to trigger workflows
- Webhook triggers for async job submission

### Processing Layer (Trigger.dev)
- Async background jobs for heavy computation
- Briefing generation: data pull → delta calc → engagement score → content assembly
- Batch engagement scoring: nightly job for all households
- Error handling with retry logic and alerts

### Notification Layer (React Email)
- Review reminders with upcoming schedule and prep status
- Attrition alerts with engagement metrics and recommendations
- Briefing ready notifications with deep links

### Deployment (Vercel)
- Edge functions for API endpoints
- Serverless functions for webhook receivers
- Environment-based configuration

## Coding Standards

### SQL (Supabase)
- Use snake_case for columns and tables
- Implement RLS policies at table creation
- Add created_at, updated_at timestamps to all tables
- Foreign key constraints with CASCADE/RESTRICT as appropriate
- Realistic engagement scoring thresholds: 0-100 scale

### TypeScript (Trigger.dev, n8n)
- Strong typing for all Salesforce API responses
- Error handling with logged context
- Pagination for API responses (Salesforce limit 2000 records/request)
- Batch processing in chunks of 100-200 records
- Exponential backoff for rate limiting

### React Email
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Responsive design for mobile/desktop
- Link to verification tokens for unsubscribe
- Include advisor contact info and timezone-aware scheduling

### n8n Workflows
- Use HTTP nodes for API calls with timeout (30s)
- Conditional nodes for change detection logic
- Loop nodes for processing arrays of records
- Error handling with email notifications to ops
- Document all API field mappings in node descriptions

## API Integration Patterns

### Salesforce
- Use OAuth2 with refresh token strategy
- Standard objects: Account (household), Contact (member), Opportunity (engagement)
- Custom objects: Portfolio__c, Review__c, BriefingLog__c
- Batch query via SOQL: SELECT ... FROM Account WHERE LastModifiedDate > :lastSync
- Field mappings: Account.Id → household.crm_id, Account.Phone → household.phone

### Custodial APIs (Schwab example)
- Use API key + OAuth for authentication
- Get accounts: /accounts (paginated)
- Get positions: /accounts/{accountId}/holdings
- Get transactions: /accounts/{accountId}/transactions?since=date
- Compute account-level deltas: new positions, closed positions, quantity changes

### Supabase (TypeScript)
- Use PostgREST for CRUD operations
- Row-level security via JWT token with user_id claim
- Real-time subscriptions for UI updates
- Raw SQL for complex analytical queries
- Connection pooling for batch operations

## Briefing Generation Logic
1. Query household + all family members from Supabase
2. Pull custodial holdings for all accounts
3. Calculate deltas: compare previous_review_date positions vs. current
4. Score engagement: last_meeting_date, activity_frequency, communication_sentiment
5. Generate conversation starters based on changes + score + cohort
6. Assemble briefing: household intro, portfolio summary, position changes, action items
7. Save to storage + Supabase (briefings table)
8. Send email to advisor with links

## Engagement Scoring Formula
- Base: 50 points
- Meeting frequency (last 90 days): +15 max
- Portfolio activity: +15 max (rebalance, new positions)
- Attrition risk: -20 to +10 (based on communication gaps, market performance)
- NPS/sentiment from notes: +10 max
- Result: Cohort assignment (0-25: at_risk, 26-50: growth, 51-75: core, 76-100: premier)

## Security & Compliance
- All data in transit: TLS 1.2+
- Credentials: environment variables, never hardcoded
- Audit logging: all briefing access logged with user + timestamp
- PII: encrypt SSN, DOB in transit
- Segregation: advisor data only accessible via assigned household RLS

## Testing & Debugging
- Use n8n test mode to validate API calls without triggering workflows
- Trigger.dev logs available in dashboard; use structured logging
- Supabase local dev: `supabase start` with local PostgreSQL
- Mock Salesforce/custodial APIs: use json-server or mock HTTP endpoints
- End-to-end: trigger sync, verify briefing generation, confirm email delivery

## Performance Targets
- Briefing generation: < 5s for typical household (< 20 positions)
- Daily sync: < 2 min for 1000 households
- Engagement batch: < 1 min for 1000 households
- Query response: < 500ms for advisor dashboard
- Email delivery: within 5 minutes of trigger

## Monitoring & Alerts
- n8n workflow failures: email ops team with error context
- Trigger.dev job failures: log to error tracking (Sentry optional)
- Supabase performance: monitor slow queries (> 1s)
- Email delivery: track open rates, link clicks via React Email
